PythonTypeScript <pre><code>from articles_sdk import sdk

sdk.setup(
    host="http://localhost:8000/api/",
    headers=lambda: {"Authorization": "Bearer token"},
)

async with sdk:
    article = await sdk.articles.get(1)
    print(article.title)          # "Why JSON:API is great"
    print(article.created_at)     # datetime — auto-converted

    await article.save(title="New title")
    await article.delete()
</code></pre> <pre><code>import { sdk } from "./articles_sdk_ts/index.js";

sdk.setup({
    host: "http://localhost:8000/api/",
    headers: async () =&gt; ({}),
});

const article = await sdk.articles.get(1);
console.log(article.title);

await article.save({ title: "New title" });
await article.delete();
</code></pre> <p>!!! tip "Why not a global singleton?" The exported <code>sdk</code> is convenient for simple apps, but a single global config is unsafe when background tasks make requests on behalf of different users (e.g., OAuth). Instantiate separate SDKs with their own config:</p> <pre><code>```python
admin_sdk = SDK(host="...", headers=lambda: {"Authorization": "Bearer " + admin_token})

user_sdk = SDK(host="...", headers=lambda: {"Authorization": "Bearer " + user_token})
```
</code></pre>

