PythonTypeScript <pre><code>articles = sdk.articles.list().fields(articles=["title", "created_at"])
# ?fields[articles]=title,created_at
</code></pre> <pre><code>const articles = sdk.articles.list().fields({
    articles: ["title", "created_at"],
});
// ?fields[articles]=title,created_at
</code></pre>

PythonTypeScript <pre><code>articles = await sdk.articles.list()
# GET /articles

# Now data is available
print(articles[0])       # first article
print(len(articles))     # count
for a in articles:       # iterate
    print(a.title)
</code></pre> <p>Accessing data before fetch raises <code>RuntimeError</code>:</p> <pre><code>col = sdk.articles.list()
col[0]  # RuntimeError: Data not fetched yet
</code></pre> <pre><code>const articles = sdk.articles.list();
await articles.fetch();
// GET /articles

console.log(articles.at(0));  // first article
console.log(articles.length); // count
for (const a of articles) {   // iterate
    console.log(a.title);
}
// Use spread for array methods
const titles = [...articles].map(a =&gt; a.title);
</code></pre>

PythonTypeScript <p><pre><code>async for article in await sdk.articles.list():
    print(article.title)
</code></pre> <code>__aiter__</code> fetches first if needed, then yields items.</p> <p><pre><code>for await (const article of sdk.articles.list()) {
    console.log(article.title);
}
</code></pre> <code>Collection</code> implements <code>AsyncIterable&lt;T&gt;</code>. Iteration triggers fetch.</p>

PythonTypeScript <pre><code>from articles_sdk.exceptions import NotFound

try:
    article = await sdk.articles.get(999)
except* NotFound as e:
    for error in e.exceptions:
        print(error.status)   # 404
        print(error.title)    # "Not Found"
        print(error.detail)   # server-provided detail message
</code></pre> <pre><code>import { NotFound } from "./articles_sdk_ts/index.js";

try {
    const article = await sdk.articles.get(999);
} catch (e) {
    if (e instanceof NotFound) {
        console.log(e.status);  // 404
        console.log(e.title);   // "Not Found"
        console.log(e.detail);  // server detail
    }
}
</code></pre>

